140 year old, 9 kilogram lobster free
'George the Giant Lobster' was captured two weeks ago.
The city's seafood company purchased it for a hundred dollars.
He instantly started using the lobster photos for his publicity.
"PETA", a group working for animal rights, demanded the release of the lobster. As a result, it will be released back into the sea.
George was caught in the sea in Canada. He then spent 10 days in the City Crab and Seafood Company tank.
The age of a lobster can be told by its weight.
The restaurant's manager, Keith Walanty, stated that their purpose was not to hurt the lobster at all. The reason to keep him in the tank was to provide entertainment for the customers.
Engrid Newkurk from the animal rights group PETA states that the restaurant's decision is worth praise and is an example for those who want to keep these precious animals in a tank or want to eat them by boiling them alive.
