Quetta, four policemen including DSP killed.
File Photo
On an important highway in Quetta, Saryab road, firing by unknown people killed four policemen, including DSP "Deputy Superintendent of Police".
Wednesday morning two DSPs, one Sub Inspector and two Constables were on the way to the Police Training Center in a jeep. On Sariab Road near Degree College an unknown rider on a motor cycle attacked the police jeep. He fired continuously. In the attack Sub Inspector Mehdi, Constables Sibgat ul llah and Nasr ul llah died on the spot. DSP Hasan Ali died after reaching the hospital.
A source at the hospital said that the second DSP, Ghulam Mohammed, is in very serious condition. He is severely injured with bullet wounds in his head and neck.
Police besieged the area after the incident. So far no one has accepted responsibility for the attack.
